text: Base Agreement # 4912065423 MSOW # 4915012201 SOW # 4915017574 Technical Services Agjreement SOW This Statement of Work #4915017574 ("SOW") adopts and incorporates by reference the terms and conditions of #4915012201 (“MSOW”) and #4912065423 (“Base Agreement”) between IBM United Kingdom Ltd (“Buyer”) and Larsen & Toubro Infotech Ltd (“Supplier”) in effect as of the date hereof. The effective date will be 1 December 2015 ("Effective Date"), and this SOW will remain in effect until the later of 31 March 2017 or until Deliverables and Services are completed. Transactions performed under this SOW will be conducted in accordance with and be subject to the terms and conditions of this SOW, the Base Agreement, and any applicable Work Authorizations (“WAs”). This SOW is not a WA. 1.0 Scope of Work Summary The scope of this engagement is to provide consulting service in the area of SAP System Analysts for the GSD Project . 2.0 Definitions Except as listed below in this Section 2.0, the definitions listed in the Base Agreement referenced above shall apply to this SOW. <Not Applicable> 3.0 Description Of Developed Works And Related Deliverables And Services SAP consultants who provide services on the BP GSD project. BP expected the consultants will work 4 days a week at BP’s site in Sunbury, UK and the fifth day from home location. Key Activity (s) and Deliverable(s) including defect resolution. Entry & exit criteria in line with the GSD Management Information using ITC2 transactions and including trials are planned during the period from October 2015 to May 2016. Support the execution of the User Acceptance Testing (UAT) & Invoice Comparison including defects resolutions. Testing to be Base Agreement # 4912065423 MSOW 4915012201 SOW # 4915017574 Coordination and completion of all deliverables associated with the Change Management work package (as per the completed deliverable tailor and waiver and the deliverable templates). Active management of the Country Change Managers/ Business Deployment Leads to ensure they have understood the planning of and are driving the delivery of the local change activities evidenced by demonstrable progress in the Country Business Readiness Plan. Any other deliverables and activities as directed by the IBM project manager to support the execution of the project 3.2 Identification of Tools Tools for the Developed Works are identified below. Supplier will update this list for all changes as soon as practicable after the change is identified. 4.0 Acceptance Criteria This will be in accordance to MSOW (Section 4.0) 5.0 Supplier's Responsibilities At all times, the Supplier will ensure availability of the SAP Consultants to ensure business continuity. In the event, where the SAP Consultants are not available due to factors like – but not limited to – unplanned leave, attrition, the Supplier will ensure continuity of deliverables and services by promptly assigning another SAP consultant. For the avoidance of doubt, the new SAP consultant would be assigned after appropriate interview and written confirmation by the Buyer Other responsibilities will be in accordance to MSOW (Section 5.0) 5.1 In addition to delivering Developed Works, and other Deliverables and Services on Schedule, Supplier will : <Not Applicable> 6.0 Quality Measurements This will be in accordance to MSOW (Section 6.0) 7.0 Buyer Responsibilities MSOW 4915012201 SOW # 4915017574 § Buyer to make sure the Key stakeholders are available and co-operate with the Supplier consultants § Buyer to share all the necessary documents regarding the system and processes § Responsibilities will in accordance to MSOW (Section 7.0) 8.0 Mutual Responsibilities § Joint governance to track the progress of engagement 9.0 Schedule for Deliverables The relevant milestones, completion dates, and terms associated with this SOW are as follows: Project duration and number of man days is based on the wider GSD project plan. Depending on the status and progress with the GSD project, Buyer reserves the right to notify Supplier to a) Amend the number of FTE days b) Terminate the contract with up to 10 working days notice 10.0 Payments The services of the consultants will be charged at a day rate of $670 (equivalent to 8 hours of work). No overtime will be charged without prior written approval from IBM Project Manager. Charges will be on a T&M basis for the services that are delivered, and are estimated at 600 days (2 FTEs) at $670 = $402,000 Expenses are expected under this SOW with a maximum of $1600 per person per week in line with BP travel policy and authorized by IBM project manager. Expense estimate for the period of the SoW is $103,000 per person, equal to $206,000 in total for 2 FTE. Summary of Labour and expense estimates Labour Charges $402,000 Expenses $206,000 Total (estimated) $608,000 Payment terms will be in accordance to MSOW (Section 9.1) MSOW 4915012201 SOW # 4915017574 11.0 Communications All communications between the parties will be carried out through the following designated coordinators or their designated successors or delegates, whom each party hereby designates as its representatives and contacts for this SOW. All notices required in writing under this Agreement will be made to the appropriate contact listed below at the following addresses and will be effective upon actual receipt. Notices may be transmitted electronically, by registered or certified mail, or courier. All notices, with the exception of legal notices, may also be provided by facsimile. The parties acknowledge that all services performed prior to the signature of this agreement have been done in good faith of the Terms and Conditions of this agreement. html:
Technical Services Agjreement SOW

This Statement of Work #4915017574 ("SOW") adopts and incorporates by reference the terms and conditions of #4915012201 ("MSOW") and #4912065423 ("Base Agreement") between IBM United Kingdom Ltd ("Buyer") and Larsen & Toubro Infotech Ltd ("Supplier") in effect as of the date hereof. The effective date will be 1 December 2015 ("Effective Date"), and this SOW will remain in effect until the later of 31 March 2017 or until Deliverables and Services are completed. Transactions performed under this SOW will be conducted in accordance with and be subject to the terms and conditions of this SOW, the Base Agreement, and any applicable Work Authorizations ("WAs"). This SOW is not a WA.

1.0 Scope of Work Summary

The scope of this engagement is to provide consulting service in the area of SAP System Analysts for the GSD Project.

2.0 Definitions

Except as listed below in this Section 2.0, the definitions listed in the Base Agreement referenced above shall apply to this SOW. <Not Applicable>

3.0 Description Of Developed Works And Related Deliverables And Services

SAP consultants who provide services on the BP GSD project. BP expected the consultants will work 4 days a week at BP's site in Sunbury, UK and the fifth day from home location.

Key Activity (s) and Deliverable(s)

Phase \ schedules

Activities / Deliverable

 

• Completion and sign off the RIEFs developments including unit tests.

 

• Completion of security build prior to the start of ITC1

 

• Support the execution of string tests of interfaces between GSD and other connected applications.

 

• Support the execution of a cycle 1 of integrated tests (ITC1) including defect resolution. Entry & exit criteria in line with the GSD Test Strategy.

 
  • • Support the execution of a cycle 1 of Month End Close and Management Information using ITC1 transactions and including defect resolution.

Execute

 
 

• Support the execution of a cycle 2 of integrated tests (ITC2) including defect resolution. Entry & exit criteria in line with the GSD Test Strategy.

 

• Support the execution of a cycle 2 of Month End Close and Management Information using ITC2 transactions and including defect resolution.

 
  • • Coordination, completion and sign off of the Data Conversions. 3 trials are planned during the period from October 2015 to May 2016.
  • • Support the execution of the User Acceptance Testing (UAT) & Invoice Comparison including defects resolutions. Testing to be completed in line with the plan.
 

• Support the execution of a UAT Month End Close and Management

Form Title: Technical Services Agreement Statement of Work (TSA_SOW)

Page 1 of 4 Revision: 5/15

Phase \ schedules

Activities / Deliverable

 

Information using UAT transactions and including defect resolution.

  • • Coordination and completion of all deliverables associated with the Change Management work package (as per the completed deliverable tailor and waiver and the deliverable templates). Active management of the Country Change Managers/ Business Deployment Leads to ensure they have understood the planning of and are driving the delivery of the local change activities evidenced by demonstrable progress in the Country Business Readiness Plan.
  • • Coordination, completion and sign off of the Cutover.
  • • Coordination, completion and sign off of the Data Conversion.
  • • Coordination, completion and sign off of the Early Life Support.

Any other deliverables and activities as directed by the IBM project manager to support the execution of the project

3.2 Identification of Tools

Tools for the Developed Works are identified below. Supplier will update this list for all changes as soon as practicable after the change is identified.
